This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object counting, which is a common task in computer vision. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel architecture for Convolutional-Deconvolutional networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

The paper also involves learning from data, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Furthermore, the use of gating units in the proposed architecture suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the evaluation of the proposed architecture on benchmark datasets suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
